the others? I'm getting hungry!

191
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:23,873
Well, Gunma... I asked
them to arrive a little late.

192
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,830
Well, I did ...

193
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:30,151
...so because I wanted
to have a talk with you.

194
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:34,197
Hiziri asked me to become ...

195
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:36,236
...his mechanic and I accepted!

196
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:40,959
- What? Why did you do that?
- Hiziri...

197
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:44,630
...will be making his
debut in Formula 3 next week.

198
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,756
And tomorrow
morning I leave with him.

199
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:49,514
From now on I can
no longer take care of your car.

200
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,955
But now you're an experienced
driver and you'll be fine.

201
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:55,154
Did you betray me just for money!

202
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,949
That's not true. That's the last
thing I was thinking of.

203
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:02,835
However I can't blame you.
It's Formula 3, after all.

204
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:06,632
So you aren't angry with me Gunma!

205
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,915
Just tell me why your doing this?

206
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,197
I'm trying with all my
might to remain calm.

207
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:15,033
I wouldn't want to
ruin my first victory.

208
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:18,439
I'm sorry, I just can't tell you!

209
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:21,950
Believe me, I want to
tell you but I just can't!

210
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:24,357
Please let me go.

211
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:27,633
- I beg of you!
- It's not fair for Gunma.

212
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:32,031
It's obvious that we cannot
stop you from going to work for Hiziri,

213
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:35,590
- but tell us why!
- He's right, Tamotsu!

214
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:38,838
That may be true but Gunma
does not swim in gold,

215
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,911
But he managed to
get a car from Kishida ...

216
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,956
...and gained his first victory!

217
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:46,314
It's true! Gunma did
everything possible...

218
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,356
...and you just can't walk away!

219
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:51,278
Well, you could at least answer me!

220
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:54,200
Don't you remember
our dreams of glory?

221
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:57,113
We started this adventure
together! Why leave?

222
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,756
It's not right to just leave us!

223
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:01,717
He's right, you know?

224
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:07,914
My feelings for you all
have not changed...

225
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,831
..since the day we met!

226
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:12,150
In fact, my dream
is identical to yours!

227
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,630
I want to travel the
world alongside Gunma!

228
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:17,672
I am sure that together we
will succeed! No, I know we will!

229
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,959
But...but...I...

230
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:26,270
Just have to do this.

231
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:31,949
Sometimes it's good to work
elsewhere for a while...

232
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:35,555
When he finally returns
to us, we'll all understand!

233
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,596
Granny,

234
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,676
You know what?

235
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:53,758
Get out, get out now.

236
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:01,269
I never want to see you again.

237
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:11,553
I will be able to win without...

238
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:14,279
...your help.
I don't need it anymore.

239
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:40,755
The checkered flag marks
the end of the race!

240
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:43,553
The car that sees the first
wave is the one that wins!

241
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,756
Winning is like living in paradise!

242
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,116
In the next episode.

243
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:50,111
Desert-colored heart?
Gunma Makes His Second Start Alone

244
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:53,272
I will not let anybody,
to overtake me!

